-- EON Russia Chairman Sergei Tazin to Step Down From Utility Posts
-- B y   A n a t o l y   T e m k i n
-- 2012-07-04T07:42:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/e-on-russia-chief-sergei-tazin-to-step-down-vedomosti-reports.html
EON Russia (EONR)  Chairman and EON Russia
Power chief Sergei Tazin is stepping down from both of the posts
as of July 6.  Tazin is leaving of his own volition and will remain an
independent board member after being elected at the utility’s
annual meeting on June 29, Anna Martynova, an EON Russia
spokeswoman, said today by phone.  The board will vote for a new chairman at its next meeting
on July 6, she said, declining to name Tazin’s replacement.  Vedomosti  newspaper reported the move earlier today, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the plans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anatoly Temkin in St. Petersburg at 
 atemkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
